  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2025-04-24",
    "date": "2025-07-08T15:26:41Z",
    "text": "National Coal Council Reestablishment Act\n\nThis bill provides statutory authority for the National Coal Council and directs the Department of Energy to reestablish the council\u00a0in accordance with the charter that was in effect on November 19, 2021. Established in 1984, the council made recommendations to DOE on matters relating to coal and the coal industry.\n\nIn addition, the bill removes the requirement under the Federal Advisory Committee Act for the council to be re-chartered every two years."
  },
